# TWITTER_CALLBACK_URL_DEV=http://localhost:5000/api/auth/twitter/callback

## ===== HOW TO SET IN RENDER =====

# Method 1: Render Dashboard (Recommended)
# 1. Go to your service in Render dashboard
# 2. Click "Environment" tab
# 3. Click "Add Environment Variable"
# 4. Enter key and value
# 5. Click "Save Changes"

# Method 2: render.yaml (Already configured)
# The render.yaml file already includes these variables
# Render will prompt you to set values during deployment

## ===== GENERATE SECURE SECRETS =====

# Use one of these methods to generate secure random strings:

# Method 1: OpenSSL (Linux/Mac/Git Bash)
# openssl rand -base64 32

# Method 2: Node.js
# node -e "console.log(require('crypto').randomBytes(32).toString('base64'))"

# Method 3: PowerShell (Windows)
# [Convert]::ToBase64String((1..32 | ForEach-Object { Get-Random -Minimum 0 -Maximum 256 }))

# Method 4: Online Generator
# https://www.random.org/strings/

## ===== IMPORTANT NOTES =====

# 1. Never commit .env files to Git
# 2. Use strong, unique secrets for production
# 3. Update ALLOWED_ORIGINS after deploying frontend
# 4. Use Internal Database URL from Render (not external)
# 5. Redeploy after changing environment variables
# 6. Keep backup of your environment variables securely
